name: Orange Pennant
description: A second orange pennant above the part of the Dutch flag that was expanded into the new region. Each r/place event, an orange pennant has been placed above the Dutch flag. The pennant can represent the orange pennant flown with the flag during national holidays. for the purpose of celebrating the royal family. It can also represent the orange outfits people wear to express their support for the Dutch national team, during international sports competitions.
